Text.Value: I will make sure it's done.
Remember all you can about devils and their contracts.
That's a problem for Wyll, not for me.
I've never seen such a fearless display of sheer idiocy. Bravo!
Ugh - heartbreaking. I bet you thought I'd be impressed.
Interesting. Now why should I go letting my favourite pet off his leash?
Never mind. We'll free Zariel's asset.
I'm not lifting another godsdamned finger for a devil.
Playtime's over. So perk up your ears - you and the pup have a new mission.
If this devil is so powerful, how did they manage to get captured?
Sounds like an easy choice to me.
They're locked up in the cult's fortress, Moonrise Towers. And you're getting 'em out.
Now get to Moonrise. And do mind the shadows - they've been especially hungry.
*You recall an old incantation from a children's story, said to void a devil's contract: 'Abi, diabole, et nunquam redi.'*
Fine, I'll play your game. But I amend the pact once the mission's done - not before.
*This may be your best chance to negotiate Wyll out of his pact.*
Say you know a pact-breaking charm and chant a series of pseudo-Infernal phrases.
You either mount a quick rescue, or you condemn Wyll to an eternity sizzling in the Hells.
Questions, questions - you're wasting my time. Let's see about getting your priorities fixed.
*Mizora's words may be flippant, but they are tinged with desperation. She cannot afford for Wyll to fail this mission.*
Compliance. Just as it should be.
Karlach, honey. If you won't do it for me, do it for him.
Think again. Clause Z, Section Thirteen - the 'Lemure' clause. Could've sworn we covered this.
'Abi, diabole, et nunquam redi.'
We could always let the cult infect the asset. I bet they'd make a loyal thrall.
I'd start caring - and quick, sunshine.
*You can think of no way to void a devil's pact.*
*You've heard of this provision - better known as the 'You First' clause.*
Forget it. This 'asset' can rot in the Towers for all I care.
Ha. Haha. Hahahahahaha!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Laughing hysterically that a player tried a children's incantation to release themselves from a devil's contract.

EditorData.AnimationTags: Mizora popping out of the ground then in to a neutral stance
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: A diabolical circle starts to draw itself on the ground. Out of it rises a hologram of Mizora, though not Mizora herself.
EditorData.SFXTags: Magic SFX from the circle appearing from ground and Mizora suddely popping out from it
EditorData.VFXTags: Magic VFX of magic circle suddenly appear and drawing on the ground.Then a hologram of Mizora popping out

Text.Value: Absolute's cult has gone and grabbed one of Zariel's assets. A devil - and a powerful one at that.
We'll rescue your asset on one condition: you end Wyll's pact.
Of course you will. Ta-ta.
Incredible - you actually think you hold the winning hand.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [gj] | Mizora's image sinks back into the ground
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Mizora's holographic image sinks into the devilish circle and it closes behind.
EditorData.SFXTags: Mizora hologram shrinks to the ground then the magic circle disappear SFX
EditorData.VFXTags: Mizora hologram shrinks to the ground then the magic circle disappear VFX

Text.Value: I'll make it simple: Wyll fails or refuses, and he turns to a thick blob of stink-flesh and sinks to Avernus.
Ahem. Clause Z, Section Thirteen: 'Should promised soul refuse obeyance or neglect duty, the pact-holder shall cast the promised into Avernus as a lemure.'
Clause F, Section Nine: 'Soul-binder shall bestow reward or favour only upon soul-bearer's fulfilment of related obligation.'

Synopsis: Mizora contacts party after she's been captured by the cultists. Not a lot of choices here, but you can try and find out how she got caught and express opinion on getting her out. This version if Wyll is not with you.
